-- BayWa Builds Its Biggest Solar Plant at Site in Bordeaux, France
-- B y   L o u i s e   D o w n i n g
-- 2013-09-17T15:08:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-17/baywa-builds-its-biggest-solar-plant-at-site-in-bordeaux-france.html
BayWa AG is building its largest
solar-power plant with enough capacity at the development near
 Bordeaux , France, to supply electricity to about 15,000 homes.  The company’s clean energy unit has begun work on the 45.4-megawatt project, Munich-based BayWa said today in an e-mailed
statement. It’s expected to start operating in July.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Louise Downing in London at 
 ldowning4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
